      <h1 class="big">About the Pastor</h1>
    	</header>
      <p><strong>Louie Santelices</strong>, Sr. Pastor of <strong>New Life in Christ Fellowship</strong> (Twin Cities) received his Master of Divinity (M.Div.) degree at <em>Bethel Seminary/University St. Paul Minnesota</em>, practiced his Mechanical Engineering degree and taught at <em>De La Salle University</em> Manila, Philippines before his call to ministry.</p>
      <p class="p_bottom_border">He served an Associate Pastor of <em>First Filipino Baptist Church of Toronto</em>, Ontario Canada (June 2010 – Mach 2014) and Pastor of <em>Filipino American Christian Church</em> (Twin Cities) (2003-2010). He also served as interim pastor, teacher, and other various capacities in several churches and organizations in the Philippines, Vancouver (BC), Montreal (PQ) and Toronto (ON), Canada.</p>
